<div id="review_3933852281" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3933852281" />
    <a title="Lauren" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11459065-lauren"><img alt="Lauren" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1586540356p2/11459065.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3933852281?book_show_action=true">Jun 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lauren" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lauren" href="/user/show/11459065-lauren">Lauren</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3933852281" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16418742788425307227">Outstanding conclusion to the disgustingly awesome “Infected” trilogy!! I came into the story a bit sad about the loss of some characters from “Contagious” and really hoped Sigler would make up for their absences. He absolutely went above and beyond - I loved both the new and old characters’ storylines, especially Cooper and Tim. The suspenseful tension gradually built up with the slower phase of scientific experiments and military planning, then totally exploded into crazy pandemic action! I ac</span>
  <span id="freeText16418742788425307227" style="display:none">Outstanding conclusion to the disgustingly awesome “Infected” trilogy!! I came into the story a bit sad about the loss of some characters from “Contagious” and really hoped Sigler would make up for their absences. He absolutely went above and beyond - I loved both the new and old characters’ storylines, especially Cooper and Tim. The suspenseful tension gradually built up with the slower phase of scientific experiments and military planning, then totally exploded into crazy pandemic action! I actually had to put the book down a few times because it made me anxious about what would happen next, haha! Lots of blood and gore, but if you’ve come this far in the trilogy, it’s nothing unexpected. So much epic action, moments of humor, squeamish scenes and a very satisfying ending. Well done!</span>
  <a data-text-id="16418742788425307227" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


